Colombia Stocks: Avianca Taca, BVC, Fabricato, Sura Rise

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-05-11T16:59:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/colombia-stocks-avianca-taca-bvc-fabricato-sura-rise.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:56 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index dropped 0.02 percent to 14,170.76 while the
Colcap Index gained 0.1 percent to 1,691.79.  Avianca Taca Holding SA (PFAVTA CB), owner of  Colombia ’s
biggest airline, gained as much as 18 percent in the first day
of trading on Colombia’s stock exchange after its share issuance
was more than five times oversubscribed. The shares rose 12
percent to 5,600 pesos after jumping to 5,900 pesos earlier.  Bolsa de Valores de Colombia (BVC)  SA, the operator of
the country’s main securities exchange, rose 1.5 percent to 41.6
pesos. Liquidity has returned to the market after Avianca Taca
and Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores (AVAL CB) ended oversubscribed
share issuances that begin trading this week, Camilo Rubiano,
analyst at Afin SA, said in a phone interview.  Textiles Fabricato Tejicondor SA (FABRI)  , Colombia’s
biggest textile maker, gained 3 percent to 51.50 pesos, its
highest in almost four years on an intraday basis, after
Colombia’s exports rose 46.5 percent in March from the same
month last year to $4.9 billion, the government statistics
agency said yesterday on its website.  Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA (GRUPOSUR)  , the
parent company of Colombia’s largest bank, climbed 1 percent to
37,260 pesos after a person familiar with the transaction said
yesterday the company plans to sell $300 million of 10-year
bonds as soon as May 12.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
